and it was some guy
in a suit outside.

00:10:14.212 --> 00:10:16.549
And when I see a guy in a suit
at my door,

00:10:16.549 --> 00:10:19.117
which has never happened,
my first thought, obviously:

00:10:19.117 --> 00:10:20.552
lottery.

00:10:20.552 --> 00:10:22.220
[laughter]

00:10:22.220 --> 00:10:23.856
And I was like,
"How much did I win?"

00:10:23.856 --> 00:10:24.956
He was like, "What?"

00:10:24.956 --> 00:10:26.558
I'm like, "How much did I win?"

00:10:26.558 --> 00:10:29.128
He was like, "Are--what's--
are you Ari Shaffir?"

00:10:29.128 --> 00:10:29.961
And I go, "Yes."

00:10:29.961 --> 00:10:31.296
And he handed me an envelope,

00:10:31.296 --> 00:10:33.465
and he goes,
"You've been served."

00:10:33.465 --> 00:10:37.236
And I was like, "I've been
served lottery winnings?"

00:10:37.236 --> 00:10:39.805
He was like, "No,
you're being sued."

00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:42.307
And I was like,
"Who's suing me?"

00:10:42.307 --> 00:10:45.344
It was the Holy Spirit.

00:10:45.344 --> 00:10:47.045
The Holy Spirit went to a court

00:10:47.045 --> 00:10:49.648
and figured out
how to sue somebody,

00:10:49.648 --> 00:10:51.650
and he sued me.

00:10:51.650 --> 00:10:52.985
He sued me!

00:10:52.985 --> 00:10:55.153
Guess how much
he sued me for.

00:10:55.153 --> 00:10:56.322 align:start size:25% position:75%
- 2,400!

00:10:56.322 --> 00:10:57.556
- $2,400.

00:10:57.556 --> 00:10:59.725
What an exact amount
you suggested.

00:10:59.725 --> 00:11:01.393
No, you didn't get it.

00:11:01.393 --> 00:11:03.829
$2,400, that'd be
a lot of money. No.

00:11:03.829 --> 00:11:06.498
He sued me for $800 million.

00:11:06.498 --> 00:11:07.532
[laughter]

00:11:07.532 --> 00:11:11.003
Yeah, $800 million

00:11:11.003 --> 00:11:14.606
was how much he sued me for.

00:11:14.606 --> 00:11:16.341
So here's the deal, you guys.

00:11:16.341 --> 00:11:19.178
I don't know if you know how
the American legal system works.

00:11:19.178 --> 00:11:22.881
But if somebody sues you,
you have to reply,

00:11:22.881 --> 00:11:25.583
or you just lose the case.

00:11:25.583 --> 00:11:30.022
And I don't have $800 million.

00:11:30.022 --> 00:11:32.458
I don't have
any million dollars.

00:11:32.458 --> 00:11:35.293
But I don't know how to reply
to a lawsuit.

00:11:35.293 --> 00:11:37.963
You'd think with all those years
of training,

00:11:37.963 --> 00:11:40.198
I would have picked up
something,

00:11:40.198 --> 00:11:42.701
but no, I did not.

00:11:42.701 --> 00:11:46.305
So I had to find a lawyer.

00:11:46.305 --> 00:11:50.809
I had to get a lawyer
to help represent me.

00:11:50.809 --> 00:11:52.444
So I call Rogan,
and I was like,

00:11:52.444 --> 00:11:55.447
"Remember the Holy Spirit?"

00:11:55.447 --> 00:11:58.150
And he was like, "No."

00:11:58.150 --> 00:11:59.818
And I'm like,
"You don't remember him?"

00:11:59.818 --> 00:12:01.620
He's like, "No.
What are you talking about?"

00:12:01.620 --> 00:12:02.988
"Remember, like,
a long time ago,

00:12:02.988 --> 00:12:05.056
"you called me one night
and you said

00:12:05.056 --> 00:12:06.892
"you needed me to be your lawyer

00:12:06.892 --> 00:12:09.561
because you were videotaping
some guy?"

00:12:09.561 --> 00:12:12.664
And he was like, "Sort of.

00:12:12.664 --> 00:12:14.633
I barely remember that."

00:12:14.633 --> 00:12:17.068
And I was like, "Okay, well,

00:12:17.068 --> 00:12:19.772
I've been representing him
for the last half decade."

00:12:19.772 --> 00:12:22.908
[laughter]

00:12:26.411 --> 00:12:28.080
"And he's suing me now."

00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:30.282
And he's like, "What?
Why did you do that?"

00:12:30.282 --> 00:12:32.517
I'm like, "A better question is,
did I win your case?

00:12:32.517 --> 00:12:35.254
And the answer is yes."

00:12:38.523 --> 00:12:41.493
So I had to find another lawyer,
and I had to hire her,

00:12:41.493 --> 00:12:44.663
and she got it thrown out.

00:12:44.663 --> 00:12:46.765
And the way she got it
thrown out was,

00:12:46.765 --> 00:12:50.102
one, it was written
in Magic Marker,

00:12:50.102 --> 00:12:52.337
which is not the standard
ink type for a lawsuit.

00:12:52.337 --> 00:12:56.108
And then she showed
the judge that,

00:12:56.108 --> 00:12:58.977
and she showed the judge
that the original amount,

00:12:58.977 --> 00:13:02.113
what he wanted to sue me for,
was not $800 million.

00:13:02.113 --> 00:13:05.818
The original amount was
"all the riches in the world."

00:13:05.818 --> 00:13:09.121
[laughter]

00:13:09.121 --> 00:13:12.858
He legit wanted to sue me
for all the riches in the world.

00:13:12.858 --> 00:13:15.394
And the court clerk
had to be like,

00:13:15.394 --> 00:13:17.395
"That's not an amount.

00:13:17.395 --> 00:13:20.299
You can't get all the riches
in the world."

00:13:20.299 --> 00:13:22.567
And they were like,
"What does that mean to you?"

00:13:22.567 --> 00:13:23.868
He's like, "Oh, 800 million."

00:13:23.868 --> 00:13:29.341
So she got it thrown out
with--with...

00:13:29.341 --> 00:13:30.309
prejudice, thank you.

00:13:30.309 --> 00:13:32.010
That sounds like
a real lawyer.

00:13:32.010 --> 00:13:34.079
You'd think I would have fucking
remembered that one.

00:13:34.079 --> 00:13:35.647
Yeah, which prejudice,
which means

00:13:35.647 --> 00:13:37.149
he can't ever sue me again.

00:13:37.149 --> 00:13:39.818
"Also, do you want
to countersue him," she said,

00:13:39.818 --> 00:13:41.420
"For damages
for putting you through this?"

00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:42.988
And I was like,
"What do you mean?"

00:13:42.988 --> 00:13:44.422
She goes, "That's what karma is,
you know?

00:13:44.422 --> 00:13:46.158
"He can't, like,
put you through this.

00:13:46.158 --> 00:13:47.592
Now he's gonna have to go
through his own thing."

00:13:47.592 --> 00:13:49.828
And I was like, "Oh, no,
karma's already...."

00:13:49.828 --> 00:13:51.730
[laughter]

00:13:51.730 --> 00:13:54.500
Like, I've never seen it
as clearly

00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:56.168
as I have right now.

00:13:56.168 --> 00:13:57.836
But, like, it's done.

00:13:57.836 --> 00:14:01.240
It already came and went back
to where it was supposed to.

00:14:01.240 --> 00:14:02.874
All right, that's my story,
everybody.

